    "millsfield:images_texts": [
      "TRANS WORKD AIRLINE\nTIVA\n605\nN 45346",
      "TWA-Transcontinental and Western Air, Inc.\nDouglas DC-4\nOriginally built as military\nC-54s, eight Skymasters were\nreleased to TWA in late 1945. Supplementing the Constella-\ntion fleet on overseas routes, the DC-4s inaugurated service\nto Cairo in 1946.\nAs more Connies were delivered,\nthe\nSkymasters also served all-cargo runs. Eventually they flew\npassenger\nand freighter flights\nsolely within the United\nStates, and all were retired by 1961. TWA operated a total of\neighteen DC-4s, naming them for points of interest on its\nsystem. Shown on this card is \"The Acropolis.\"\nPublished by Aviation World, Inc., P.O. Box 188, Bethel, Conn. 06801 U.S.A.\nD-005\n55788-D\npost card\nPhoto courtesy of Trans World Airlines\nN45346 C/N 27350\n2002.113.474"
    ],
